# Frontend State Management

**Rule: Server state and client state must NEVER be mixed.**

## Taxonomy

| State Type | Tool | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| Server / async | TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) | Bookings list, menu items, table availability |
| UI / ephemeral client | Zustand store | Cart contents, selected table, modal open state, active filters |

## TanStack Query — Server State

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT — query key is structured [scope, id?, params?]
const { data: booking } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['bookings', bookingId],
  queryFn: () => api.getBooking(bookingId),
  staleTime: 30_000,
});

// ✅ CORRECT — mutation invalidates related queries
const { mutate: createBooking } = useMutation({
  mutationFn: api.createBooking,
  onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['bookings'] }),
});
```

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — storing API response in useState
const [bookings, setBookings] = useState([]);
useEffect(() => { fetch('/api/bookings').then(...).then(setBookings) }, []);
```

## Zustand — Client State

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT — one store per domain slice; NO server data stored here
interface CartStore {
  items: OrderItem[];
  addItem: (item: OrderItem) => void;
  clearCart: () => void;
}
export const useCartStore = create<CartStore>((set) => ({
  items: [],
  addItem: (item) => set((s) => ({ items: [...s.items, item] })),
  clearCart: () => set({ items: [] }),
}));
```

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — fetching inside Zustand and storing remote data
fetchBookings: async () => {
  const data = await api.getBookings(); // server state belongs in TanStack Query
  set({ bookings: data });
}
```

## Rules
- ❌ NEVER call `fetch`/`axios` directly inside a Zustand action
- ❌ NEVER cache API responses in `useState` or Zustand
- ✅ Query keys must be arrays; use `@shared/query-keys.ts` constants
- ✅ Optimistic updates are allowed in `useMutation` `onMutate` with rollback in `onError`
- ✅ Socket.IO real-time events should update TanStack Query cache via `queryClient.setQueryData`
